<catsoop-section>Introduction</catsoop-section>

Ever wondered how computers sort random things into order so quickly? We often work with ordered lists, making information easier to find. Telephone directories, dictionaries, and book indexes use alphabetical order for convenience. Without sorting, finding information would be much more complicated. Despite their speed, computers have limits on how quickly they can solve problems, but they sort things with the help of a sorting map.

<catsoop-section>Materials Required</catsoop-section>

- Chalks

<catsoop-section>Instructions</catsoop-section>

1. Draw a given sorting map on land by chalk or any other thing.

2. Randomly 4 students take pen paper and write any number on paper.

3. Now one student will stand up in one rectangular box each.

4. As shown by arrow two students from first two boxes will come in first circle and last two rectangle's students will come in second circle.

5. Now from both circles the student who has the least number will go to the circle denoted by the green arrow and the student who has greater number will go to the circle denoted by the red arrow.

6. Again the smaller number goes to the first rectangular box and the greater number goes to the last rectangular box. Thus we get the least and the greatest number.

7. Remaining numbers go to the next circle. Again they will be distributed by a small number that goes next to the least number's rectangle and greater number will go before the greatest number's rectangular box.

8. Now see the result of the last rectangular boxes.

<catsoop-section>What's Happening</catsoop-section>

Here at first we sort smaller and bigger numbers from the first two and last two rectangular boxes. Then again we sort smaller and bigger numbers from these smaller numbers circle and bigger numbers circle. By this way we got the smallest to biggest number in ascending order.

This is called a **sorting network** â€” a fixed sequence of comparisons that sorts any input. Computers use similar algorithms to sort data efficiently!

